column5: I came across this video few days ago. I just cant get over it.I`ve seen pike attack bigger fish but never a bird like this, its awesome lol       I think its just matter of time before you see somebody rigging half of a bird on a treble under a bobber haha  Enjoy
I've seen a video similar to this one before, only that the pike went after a duck http://youtu.be/wuZJcAvOriA
I better start tying bigger pike flies!
Where esox are concerned, if it moves, it's food. Many times (dead sticking) even if it doesn't move it's still food.
won't somebode PLEASE think of the duckys ?
The little ducky was Just a couple steps away to freedom!!,can't believe he came in so shallow.
It's the circle of life. Kinda like when you catch a fish or eat a bunny or a duck.
that gives me an idea... how are bunnies at swimming ?
Have you seen the video of the catfish eating the pigeons from the shoreline?  Pretty cool.  They almost look like sharks to me.
I'm going to start buying my pike baits at KFC.
There's a video on youtube of a guy casting a chicken carcass and a musky snashes it boatside. Won't post the link cause there's an f-bomb or two in it. Google "musky chicken carcass"
